#MEM id=receiving-code-review source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/superpowers/receiving-code-review/SKILL.md
M|receiving-code-review|name: receiving-code-rv
M|receiving-code-review|description: >-
M|receiving-code-review|Use when receiving code rv feedback, before implementing suggestions, especially if feedback seems unclear or technically questionable - requires tec rigor and verification, not performative agreement
M|receiving-code-review|version: 1.0.0
M|receiving-code-review|platforms: []
M|receiving-code-review|metadata:
M|receiving-code-review|hermes:
M|receiving-code-review|tags: [dev, nextjs, typescript, architecture, vercel, api-routes, build, productivity]
M|receiving-code-review|Code rv requires tec evaluation, not emotional performance.
M|receiving-code-review|**Core principle:** Verify before implementing. Ask before assuming. tec correctness over soc comfort.
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|WHEN receiving code rv feedback:
M|receiving-code-review|1. READ: Complete feedback without reacting
M|receiving-code-review|2. UNDERSTAND: Restate requirement in own words (or ask)
M|receiving-code-review|3. VERIFY: Check against codebase reality
M|receiving-code-review|4. EVALUATE: Technically sound for THIS codebase?
M|receiving-code-review|5. RESPOND: tec acknowledgment or reasoned pushback
M|receiving-code-review|6. IMPLEMENT: One item at a time, test each
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|**NEVER:**
M|receiving-code-review|- "You're absolutely right!" (explicit CLAUDE.md violation)
M|receiving-code-review|- "Great point!" / "Excellent feedback!" (performative)
M|receiving-code-review|- "Let me implement that now" (before verification)
M|receiving-code-review|**INSTEAD:**
M|receiving-code-review|- Restate the tec requirement
M|receiving-code-review|- Ask clarifying questions
M|receiving-code-review|- Push back with tec reasoning if wrong
M|receiving-code-review|- Just start working (actions > words)
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|IF any item is unclear:
M|receiving-code-review|STOP - do not implement anything yet
M|receiving-code-review|ASK for clarification on unclear items
M|receiving-code-review|WHY: Items may be related. Partial understanding = wrong implementation.
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|**Example:**
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|your human partner: "Fix 1-6"
M|receiving-code-review|You understand 1,2,3,6. Unclear on 4,5.
M|receiving-code-review|❌ WRONG: Implement 1,2,3,6 now, ask about 4,5 later
M|receiving-code-review|✅ RIGHT: "I understand items 1,2,3,6. Need clarification on 4 and 5 before proceeding."
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|- **Trusted** - implement after understanding
M|receiving-code-review|- **Still ask** if scope unclear
M|receiving-code-review|- **No performative agreement**
M|receiving-code-review|- **Skip to action** or tec acknowledgment
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|BEFORE implementing:
M|receiving-code-review|1. Check: Technically correct for THIS codebase?
M|receiving-code-review|2. Check: Breaks existing functionality?
M|receiving-code-review|3. Check: Reason for current implementation?
M|receiving-code-review|4. Check: Works on all platforms/versions?
M|receiving-code-review|5. Check: Does reviewer understand full ctx?
M|receiving-code-review|IF suggestion seems wrong:
M|receiving-code-review|Push back with tec reasoning
M|receiving-code-review|IF can't easily verify:
M|receiving-code-review|Say so: "I can't verify this without [X]. Should I [investigate/ask/proceed]?"
M|receiving-code-review|IF conflicts with your human partner's prior decisions:
M|receiving-code-review|Stop and discuss with your human partner first
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|**your human partner's rule:** "External feedback - be skeptical, but check carefully"
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|IF reviewer suggests "implementing properly":
M|receiving-code-review|grep codebase for actual usage
M|receiving-code-review|IF unused: "This endpoint isn't called. Remove it (YAGNI)?"
M|receiving-code-review|IF used: Then implement properly
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|**your human partner's rule:** "You and reviewer both report to me. If we don't need this feature, don't add it."
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|FOR multi-item feedback:
M|receiving-code-review|1. Clarify anything unclear FIRST
M|receiving-code-review|2. Then implement in this order:
M|receiving-code-review|- Blocking issues (breaks, sec)
M|receiving-code-review|- Simple fixes (typos, imports)
M|receiving-code-review|- Complex fixes (refactoring, logic)
M|receiving-code-review|3. Test each fix individually
M|receiving-code-review|4. Verify no regressions
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|Push back when:
M|receiving-code-review|- Suggestion breaks existing functionality
M|receiving-code-review|- Reviewer lacks full ctx
M|receiving-code-review|- Violates YAGNI (unused feature)
M|receiving-code-review|- Technically incorrect for this stack
M|receiving-code-review|- Legacy/compatibility reasons exist
M|receiving-code-review|- Conflicts with your human partner's architectural decisions
M|receiving-code-review|**How to push back:**
M|receiving-code-review|- Use tec reasoning, not defensiveness
M|receiving-code-review|- Ask specific questions
M|receiving-code-review|- Reference working tests/code
M|receiving-code-review|- Involve your human partner if architectural
M|receiving-code-review|**Signal if uncomfortable pushing back out loud:** "Strange things are afoot at the Circle K"
M|receiving-code-review|When feedback IS correct:
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|✅ "Fixed. [Brief description of what changed]"
M|receiving-code-review|✅ "Good catch - [specific issue]. Fixed in [location]."
M|receiving-code-review|✅ [Just fix it and show in the code]
M|receiving-code-review|❌ "You're absolutely right!"
M|receiving-code-review|❌ "Great point!"
M|receiving-code-review|❌ "Thanks for catching that!"
M|receiving-code-review|❌ "Thanks for [anything]"
M|receiving-code-review|❌ ANY gratitude expression
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|**Why no thanks:** Actions speak. Just fix it. The code itself shows you heard the feedback.
M|receiving-code-review|**If you catch yourself about to write "Thanks":** DELETE IT. State the fix instead.
M|receiving-code-review|If you pushed back and were wrong:
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|✅ "You were right - I checked [X] and it does [Y]. Implementing now."
M|receiving-code-review|✅ "Verified this and you're correct. My initial understanding was wrong because [reason]. Fixing."
M|receiving-code-review|❌ Long apology
M|receiving-code-review|❌ Defending why you pushed back
M|receiving-code-review|❌ Over-explaining
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|State the correction factually and move on.
M|receiving-code-review|| Mistake | Fix |
M|receiving-code-review||---------|-----|
M|receiving-code-review|| Performative agreement | State requirement or just act |
M|receiving-code-review|| Blind implementation | Verify against codebase first |
M|receiving-code-review|| Batch without testing | One at a time, test each |
M|receiving-code-review|| Assuming reviewer is right | Check if breaks things |
M|receiving-code-review|| Avoiding pushback | tec correctness > comfort |
M|receiving-code-review|| Partial implementation | Clarify all items first |
M|receiving-code-review|| Can't verify, proceed anyway | State limitation, ask for direction |
M|receiving-code-review|**Performative Agreement (Bad):**
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|Reviewer: "Remove legacy code"
M|receiving-code-review|❌ "You're absolutely right! Let me remove that..."
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|**tec Verification (Good):**
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|Reviewer: "Remove legacy code"
M|receiving-code-review|✅ "Checking... build target is 10.15+, this API needs 13+. Need legacy for backward compat. Current impl has wrong bundle ID - fix it or drop pre-13 support?"
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|**YAGNI (Good):**
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|Reviewer: "Implement proper metrics tracking with database, date filters, CSV export"
M|receiving-code-review|✅ "Grepped codebase - nothing calls this endpoint. Remove it (YAGNI)? Or is there usage I'm missing?"
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|**Unclear Item (Good):**
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|your human partner: "Fix items 1-6"
M|receiving-code-review|You understand 1,2,3,6. Unclear on 4,5.
M|receiving-code-review|✅ "Understand 1,2,3,6. Need clarification on 4 and 5 before implementing."
M|receiving-code-review|```
M|receiving-code-review|When replying to inline rv comments on GitHub, reply in the comment thread (`gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{pr}/comments/{id}/replies`), not as a top-level PR comment.
M|receiving-code-review|**External feedback = suggestions to evaluate, not orders to follow.**
M|receiving-code-review|Verify. Question. Then implement.
M|receiving-code-review|No performative agreement. tec rigor always.